id: pm-csv-ik4l
title: "Fix --no-header: host rejects bare --no- flag as negation of missing --header"
description: "pm csv export --no-header (and csv-export export --no-header) failed with 'Unknown option --header' / silently ignored, because the pm host parses --no-X as the negation of a registered --X flag. The export command declared a bare { long: '--no-header' } which the host never matched. Fix: declare the positive --header flag (host now accepts --no-header as its negation, setting header=false) and read ctx.options.header===false in both the command and exporter-capability paths. Added a regression test asserting the export command declares --header not --no-header. Verified end-to-end: --no-header omits the header row, default keeps it; 59/59 tests pass."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-04T23:11:36.126Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T09:57:20.020Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-18T09:57:20.019Z"
author: codex
resolution: index.ts declares the positive --header flag and handles header===false
expected_result: csv export declares --header flag
actual_result: "Regression test test/smoke.test.ts:42-63 asserts --header declared, not bare --no-header (verified 2026-07-18)"
